(29, 12, 'upload/servicegallery/d5929681019b1e5e4b1a.jpg', 'HEALTHY LIFESTYLE.\r\nYou are what you eat!!\r\nFacts\r\n.Thanks to God for creating onions which provide treatment for Epistaxis a medical name for nosebleeds.\r\nWhat to do:\r\n*Cut an onion into thick slices\r\n*Press one onion under your nose\r\n*Inhale the fumes\r\nWithin a few minutes the bleeding is done.\r\nIf it doesnt stop within 15 to 25 minutes seek a medical attention\r\n.Did you know one of the causes of the back injury at work is lifting objects while bending your back.\r\nBend your knees and not your waist.\r\nYou are too young to complain of backaches.\r\nTHE TRUTH ABOUT\r\nApples\r\nGet whiter and healthier teeth by biting and chewing an apple.\r\nA bite and a chew, reduces tooth decay by lowering the levels of a bacteria.\r\nAvoid Alzheimer by drinking apple juice. It fights the effects of aging on he brain.\r\nDecrease the risk of diabetes by eating at least one apple a day. Has soluble fibre, the key to blunting blood sugar swings. \r\nBeing overweight, comes along with many health problems like, heart disease, stroke and sleep apnea.\r\nManage your weight with an apple which is rich in fibre that helps to control it.\r\nDad, do you like baked apples? Yes son, why\r\nThe orchard is on fire.\r\n\r\nYoghurt\r\nAs you age, you need more protein to keep your skin healthy as well as fighting off illness. Yoghurt is a great way to boost your protein levels.\r\nYoghurt is rich in Vitamin B12, necessary for energy and healthy brain function. Say yes to yoghurt.\r\nBeing widely accepted as a healthy choice for breakfast, those who take it benefit from live bacteria cultures, so called, good bacteria. The bacteria cultures like probiotics help regulate the digestive system as well as regularizing bowel functions.\r\nWhy not? Treat yourself for a healthy you.\r\nIve got more important things to think about. Ive got a yoghurt to finish by today, the expiry date is today.\r\nCakes\r\nYou are familiar with wedding cakes, I guess, and probably you dont know the benefits you bring yourself when having it.\r\nCakes are mixed with lot of ingredients containing different nutrients suitable for our bodies.\r\nFlour and sugar contained in cakes are a source of energy since they are carbohydrates.\r\nThere are cakes that contain apples and berries which are a source of fiber. This helps in improved digestion.\r\nPlease dont dwell too much on cakes. Take a balanced diet for a healthy you. \r\nThe first wedding cakes were actually loaves of bread.\r\nStrawberries\r\nStrawberries are particularly healthy fruits. They have inspired the flavor in products like fragrances, ice creams and soaps.\r\nThey contain fiber to help in digestive system. \r\nGood source of manganese to maintain healthy bones.\r\nAn addition of strawberries on your whole grain toast is delicious especially when sliced on top.\r\nStrawberries are the only fruits that have seeds located on the outside. About 200 of them.\r\nBeetroots\r\nBeetroot taste is sweet and tender to eat. It has greatly featured in recipes from professional chefs locally and globally.\r\nBeetroot juice increases blood flow to the brain thus maintaining a healthy working brain.\r\nNitrates found in beets helps in blood flow and blood pressure.\r\nBetaine from beets, helps protect cells, internal organs as well as fighting inflammation.\r\nIf you start drinking beet juice, know that it may make your urine and stools look reddish. Its normal.\r\n5\r\n Super Lifestyle tips\r\n\r\n\r\nYour dry lips and mouth could be as a result of little water intake. Drink 2-3 litres of water daily.\r\nLearn to appreciate God, family and friends. Your moods can be lifted.\r\nI know you wouldnt want premature aging, right? Get enough sleep\r\nClimb stairs instead of taking the lift. Thats exercise.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2017-01-17 05:37:24'),
(30, 19, 'upload/servicegallery/e69e295f3f084a7a2485.jpg', 'Cover programming topics as well as C++. Traditional textbooks do a pretty good job of teaching the basics of a given programming language, but they often do not cover relevant programming topics that are incidental to the language. For example, books will omit sections on programming style, common pitfalls, debugging, good/bad programming practices, and testing. Consequently, by the time you finish the book, you understand how to program in a language, but you have a ton of bad habits that will come back to bite you later! One of the goals of these tutorials is to make sure that all of these incidental topics are covered along the way, in the sections where it naturally makes sense to discuss them. When you finish, you will not only know how to program in C++, you will know how NOT to program in C++, which is arguably as important.\r\nProvide a lot of examples. Most people learn as much or more from following the examples as they do from reading the text. This tutorial will endeavor to provide plenty of clear, concise examples to show how to apply the concepts you are learning. We will also avoid (as much as possible) the twin evils: the magic hand wave (also known as ), where in the interest of space part of an example is omitted, and the unexplained new concept, where a new concept that is integral to the example is introduced without any mention of what it is or how it works. Both of these tend to lead to getting stuck.\r\nProvide practice programs. The end of many lessons and sections will contain some exercises that you can attempt to answer on your own, along with solutions. You can compare your solution against ours to see what we did differently, or, if you get stuck, how we solved the problem. Then you can go back and refocus on the areas you need more work on.\r\nMost importantly: have fun. Programming can be a lot of fun, and if youre not generally having fun, youre not in the right mindset to b